						               													<description>&amp;quot;Fight For Tobruk !&amp;quot; is a conflict simulation of Rommel's attack on Tobruk in June 1942. The game is based on Conflict Game Company's &amp;quot;The Fall of Tobruk&amp;quot; but is not a reproduction, according to the designer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Fight For Tobruk !&amp;quot; is an operational level wargame in which each turn represents one day, each hex represents 170 meters, and units are companies or battalions. The components include:&amp;#10;-  B&amp;amp;W cardstock coversheet&amp;#10;-  six-page rulebook containing two pages of rules, a blank page, setup instructions, designer's notes, tables, charts and OOB&amp;#10;-  B&amp;amp;W cardstock game turn track&amp;#10;-  yellow cardstock A4-sized hex map&amp;#10;-  cardstock sheet containing 53 uncut counters in two colors&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fredrik Malmberg started Wellington Wargames (later Swedish Games Production) at 14 and published a wargaming magazine, &amp;quot;The Combat&amp;quot;.  &amp;quot;Fight For Tobruk !&amp;quot; was his second design, with 1,000 copies being printed and mimeographed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
